column5: Any reports on water temp for Lac Seul would be appreciated!!! Thanks
anywhere from 54-60deg. Supposed to get sunny the next 4 days so we'll watch it shoot up to the mid 60's and the walleye bite should really get going.

Just got back from fishing north shore last week. Had tough time finding temps on main lake above 49 degrees. Late in week it got up to 53 degrees. Should be warming up and getting better when I go back 1st week of July. Mike Kansas
Can you give me a report on water levels?
Lac Seul water levels can be found here:http://www.lwcb.ca/pdf/LacSeulGraph2008.06.16.pdf The lake is way ahead of the levels at this time last year. Regards,
Thanks Mike and Ben This is just like fishing, someone hijacks a thread just like they hijack your hot spot I digress I'm gone to Canada....Thank God!!!
